org.foxlabs.validation.constraint

Class ConstraintComposition<V>

  • java.lang.Object
    • org.foxlabs.validation.AbstractValidation<V>
      • org.foxlabs.validation.constraint.ConstraintAggregation<V>
        • org.foxlabs.validation.constraint.ConstraintComposition<V>
  • Type Parameters:
    V - The type of value to be validated
    All Implemented Interfaces:
    Constraint<V>, Validation<V>

    public final class ConstraintComposition<V>
extends ConstraintAggregation<V>
    This class provides ConstraintAggregation implementation that is composition of the encapsulated constraints.

    This class differs from the ConstraintConjunction in that it returns error message composed from messages of the encapsulated constraints (each message in a new line).

    Author:
    Fox Mulder
    See Also:
    Composition, ConstraintFactory.join(Constraint...), ConstraintFactory.join(Class, Constraint...), ConstraintFactory.join(java.util.Collection), ConstraintFactory.join(Class, java.util.Collection)
